{
  "texts": [
    "The parameter η, which has units of inverse length squared, introduces an IR modification that becomes relevant at cosmological scales.",
    "(1), one obtains the corresponding uncertainty relation",
    "which, unlike the standard HUP, is not minimized when ∆x → 0, but instead admits a nonzero lower bound on momentum uncertainty.",
    "By minimizing the right hand side of Eq.",
    "(3), we obtain the minimal measurable momentum ∆p min = ℏ |η|."
  ]
}